= SDL_RenderSetLogicalSize =
Use this function to set a device independent resolution for rendering.




== Syntax ==
<syntaxhighlight lang='c++'>
int SDL_RenderSetLogicalSize(SDL_Renderer* renderer,
                             int           w,
                             int           h)
</syntaxhighlight>


== Function Parameters ==
{|
|'''renderer'''
|the renderer for which resolution should be set
|-
|'''w'''
|the width of the logical resolution
|-
|'''h'''
|the height of the logical resolution
|}


== Return Value ==
Returns 0 on success or a negative error code on failure; call [[SDL_GetError]]() for more information.



